@node "REGISTER" "How to register"
@next "KEYFILE"
@prev "COPYRIGHTS"

  @{u}It is possible to register in two ways:@{uu}

  1) @{u}via snail mail@{uu}

     - You can pay by remittance or with a cheque.
     - The @{"keyfile" link "KEYFILE" 0} will be sent on a disk (HD or DD).
       Please send me an Amiga-formatted disk and a prepaid envelope with your
       address. You will then get the latest version of TUMMY.
     - The @{"registration form" system "ed TUMMY.regist"} can be placed on the disk as ASCII-file or added
       separately as a print-out.

  2) @{u}via eMail@{uu}

     - You can pay by remittance or with a cheque.
     - The @{"keyfile" link "KEYFILE" 0} will be send via eMail. Obviously you have to enter your
       eMail address in the @{"registration form" system "ed TUMMY.regist"}.
       The current T.U.M.M.Y. version will not be sent by eMail, however you can
       always find it in Aminet or on my homepage.
     - Please send the @{"registration form" system "ed TUMMY.regist"} as an ASCII-file to my
       @{"eMail address" link "AUTOR" 0}.

  Registrations and @{"keyfile" link "KEYFILE" 0}-distribution via eMail are handled with priority,
  however I will try to handle snail mail registrations as fast as possible.

  See also the @{"copyright terms" link "COPYRIGHTS" 0} and the @{"registration form" system "ed TUMMY.regist"}!

@endnode

@node "KEYFILE" "Keyfiles` function"
@next "AUTOR"
@prev "REGISTER"

  @{b}As a registered user you will get a keyfile that contains your name
  and a specific personal code.@{ub}

  If this file is not found or is defective you may only test the program
  but not use it regularily. A small requester will pop up from time to
  time to remind you of the unregistered status of the program.

  @{u}Notice@{uu}: The keyfile is for your personal use only! Do not give
  it to anyone else!

  @{b}Place the keyfile into the program's directory.@{ub}
  When next executed, the program will find the keyfile and check it
  automatically.

  See also the @{"copyright terms" link "COPYRIGHTS" 0}!

@endnode

