@node "FUTURE" "Planned extensions"
@next "PROGRAMMTEILE"
@prev "VERSIONEN"

  First of all I must admit that I cannot guarantee any further development
  of this program.

  Notice: This heavily depends on new registrations.

  @{u}The following modifications and extensions are planned:@{uu}

  - A WarpUp PPC version.

  - General optimizations.

  - Frequently database updates

  - Many new functions (e.g. predefined filter configurations to
    search for tournament legal cards and many more)

@endnode

@node "PROGRAMMTEILE" "T.U.M.M.Y files"
@next "FENSTER"
@prev "FUTURE"

  @{u}You should have the following files along with T.U.M.M.Y:@{uu}
       
  @{b}TUMMY@{ub}                              (root directory)
    |
    +-TUMMY                          (the main executable)
    |
    +-@{b}Docs@{ub}                           (directory for the document files)
    |  |
    |  +-@{b}English@{ub}-+-TUMMY.guide       (the hypertext-help in English)
    |  |         +-TUMMY.regist      (the registration form in English)
    |  |       
    |  +-@{b}Deutsch@{ub}-+-TUMMY.guide       (the hypertext-help in German)
    |            +-TUMMY.regist      (the registration form in German)
    |
    +-@{b}Catalogs@{ub}                       (directory containing all catalogs)
    |  |
    |  +-@{b}English@{ub}--TUMMY.catalog      (directory for the english catalog)
    |  +-@{b}Deutsch@{ub}--TUMMY.catalog      (directory for the german catalog)
    |
    +-@{b}Config@{ub}                         (directory for the configuration files)
    |  |
    |  +-#?.config                   (the different configuration files)
    |
    +-@{b}Icons@{ub}                          (directory for the icons used)
    |  |
    |  +-TUMMY.AppIcon               (the Iconify-icon)
    |
    +-@{b}AFD@{ub}                            (directory for the AFD-files)
    |  |
    |  +-AFD-COPYRIGHT               (@{"Copyright terms" link "COPYRIGHTS" 0} in English)
    |  +-AFD-COPYRIGHT.#?            (@{"Copyright terms" link "COPYRIGHTS" 0} in other languages)
    |
    .
    .
    .
    +-TUMMY.key                      (Your @{"keyfile" link "KEYFILE" 0} if you @{"registriered" link "REGISTER" 0}!)
      
@endnode

@node "DEVELOP" "Developer infos"
@next "FENSTER"
@prev "PROGRAMMTEILE"

  The ARexx port. This interface supports several @{"comands" link "AREXX" 0} that may also control the user
  interface and is availabe as command host as well as function host.
  For more information about ARexx please consult your Amiga ARexx User Guide
  or similiar books.

  The Arexx port is available for registered user only.

  The names of these ports are displayed in the information requester.

  Only a few commands are available at the moment however registered users
  may request additional commands.

@endnode

@node "FENSTER" "The various windows"
@next "MAIN"
@prev "DEVELOP"

  The application uses several windows, each covering specific functions. All
  can be closed by either pressing the close gadget or using the <Esc>-key.

  One exception is the itself. Closing this one means leaving TUMMY.

  The <Tab>-key activates the first text or numeric gadget of the active
  window.

  Most of the functions that you can see in the windows are also available
  as a menu item and therefore also have a shortcut (which you can lookup
  in the menu).

@endnode

@node "NID_SystemGadget" "System gadgets"

  This is a system gadget, created by the operating system. Please have
  a look at your AmigaOS manual for its function.

@endnode

@node "AREXX" "Index of the supported arexx commands"

  @{u}The standard return codes (RC) are:@{uu}

  0   RC_OK      No errors. Returned by all functions on successful completion.

  5   RC_WARN    TUMMY was not able to process the command completely. The cause
                 depends on the function. Not returned by all functions.

  10  RC_ERROR   Processing of the command was stopped due to an error. May also
                 be returned if the given command is unknown or a wrong argument
                 list was supplied. Returned by all functions.

  20  RC_FATAL   Fatal error. Returned if the port is not able to accept a command,
                 e.g. if TUMMY is currently closed down.

  No function will return a secondary result (using RESULT) at the moment.


  @{u}T.U.M.M.Y knows the following ARexx commands:@{uu}

  QUIT [REQUEST]
    Quits the program.

    REQUEST
      Open a requester that asks the user if s/he really wants to quit TUMMY.

    Result: RC


  ICONIFY
    Iconify the program.
    All windows will be closed and an icon appears on the Workbench. If the
    program is already iconified this command is ignored.

    Result: RC


  UNICONIFY
    The user interface is re-opened.
    If the program is currently not iconified this command is ignored.

    Result: RC

@endnode




